author: @CurlyQ97
text: If you are having issues with publishing your GitHub site because of a Jekyll error, I have figured it out and hope to be able to help others struggling.  Go to the settings in VSC, type 'newline', and select the box saying you want a newline inserted automatically. Once this is selected, close and restart VSC. Save everything all over again, then do the process of uploading it to Github.   My error was under assets --> css --> noscript.css  There wasn't a newline at the very bottom. Manually adding a blank line at the bottom won't change it, unfortunately.  I hope this helps most of you!!
